Polpharma Wins Exclusive Talks on Polfa, Rzeczpospolita Reports

-- B y   M o n i k a   R o z l a l
-- 
2011-09-28T05:32:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/polpharma-wins-exclusive-talks-on-polfa-rzeczpospolita-reports.html
Poland’s Polpharma SA outbid
Actavis Group HF and three other companies to win exclusive
talks on acquiring Polfa Warszawa SA, a Warsaw-based drugmaker,
 Rzeczpospolita  reported, citing Artur Wozniak, who heads the
state-owned Polski Holding Farmaceutyczny SA that controls
Polfa.  Wozniak told the newspaper the price and some employee
rights have already been agreed and Polpharma will negotiate a
social package with labor unions.  Polpharma also outbid ZF Adamed Pharma SA, Ukraine’s
Arterium Korporatsiya and  China ’s Harbin Pharmaceutical Group
Co., Rzeczpospolita said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Monika Rozlal in Warsaw at 
 mrozlal@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  